 the type of dark matter halos we expect to host a\ndestroyed ``stellar halo progenitor'' dwarf, a surviving dIrr, and a surviving\ndSph galaxy, and show that their derived abundance patterns, stellar masses,\nand gas masses are consistent with those observed for each type of system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Jan 2005 22:07:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 19 Dec 2005 16:40:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
